            <h1>About This Project</h1>

            <div class="content">
                <p>This website tracks JStyles' daily activity patterns, specifically focusing on time spent in bed versus being productive. It's a fun project that combines hardware sensors and web development.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-box">
                <h2>What it displays</h2>
                <p>The current status has three states:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Being Productive 💪 - Bed sensor is off</li>
                    <li>Being Lazy 🛏️ - Bed sensor is on </li>
                    <li>Sleeping 😴 - Phone is off, time is between 10pm and 9am, and bedsensor is on. </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-box">
                <h2>How It Works</h2>
                <p>The system uses:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Custom bed sensor using esphome</li>
                    <li>Homeassistant for logging</li>
                    <li>Web interface for status display</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-box">
                <h2>Technical Details</h2>
                <p>Built with:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Python Fastapi backend</li>
                    <li>Jinja2 templating</li>
                    <li>Homeassistant api integration</li>
                    <li>Real-time data updates (Every 120 seconds)</li>
                </ul>
